text.tspan: What I mean by "neutrality" and how to achieve global peace
China and Taiwan are on opposite sides of neutrality,
while Hong Kong seems to be on the line of neutrality

flowRoot.flowPara: Reason: USSR and USA had opposing ideologies during the Cold War. Ukraine was under USSR influence during the Cold War, but historically it has been a "borderland" since its origin in the 14th Century (after Mongolian occupation).

Reason: Mainland China became communist after the civil war and remains so throughout the Cold War. China's communism inherited from USSR's influence and aide. Taiwan recieved help from USA and adopted American-style democracy and political system. Whereas, Hong Kong was excluded from the turmoil of the civil war and Cold War because it was a British colony, that ended in 1997 (after the collapse of Soviet Union in 1991).
➊ The solution for a peaceful future does not exist in the old, Cold-War mindset
➋ The future should move towards multi-polar, globally egalitarian
➌ The former "Eastern bloc" lacks justification to expand its sphere of influence if its political system remains old-fashioned, totalitarian and isolationist

➍ Western-style democracy in the narrow sense of mass voting is not a complete political system, but democracy is a desirable value to be introduced to other countries if balanced by additional values such as free market and racial equality.
